  "content": " other. The real gap only shows on short-text batches — and that's a CPU startup cost, not a sustained difference.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">04 / 08</div>\n</div>\n<!-- SLIDE 5: THE SURPRISE — CSS memory architecture diagram -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">The Surprise</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 16px;\">\n    The Integrated GPU<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-cyan\">Beat the Discrete GPU.</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 24px;\">\n    51ms vs 56ms. Not huge — but consistent. The diagram below shows why.\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- CSS ARCHITECTURE DIAGRAM — side-by-side data flow comparison -->\n  <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">\n\n    <!-- LEFT COLUMN: iGPU path (zero copy) -->\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; position: relative;\">\n      <!-- Column header -->\n      <div style=\"text-align: center; margin-bottom: 16px;\">\n        <div style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 6px 20px; border-radius: 20px; background: rgba(6,182,212,0.15); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent-cyan); letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase;\">iGPU Path</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <!-- Input text -->\n      <div style=\"background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px 18px; text-align: center; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary);\">\n        Input text\n      </div>\n\n      <!-- Arrow down (short, green) -->\n      <div style=\"display: flex; justify-content: center; padding: 6px 0;\">\n        <div style=\"width: 3px; height: 24px; background: var(--accent-green); border-radius: 2px; position: relative;\">\n          <div style=\"position: absolute; bottom: -6px; left: 50%; transform: tran